definition.value: The practice of making only a perfunctory or symbolic effort to be inclusive to members of minority groups, especially by recruiting a small number of people from underrepresented groups in order to give the appearance of racial or sexual equality within a workforce. The effort of including a token employee to a workforce is usually intended to create the impression of social inclusiveness and diversity (racial, religious, sexual, etc.) in order to deflect accusations of discrimination.

A type of tokenism in media in which a minority person or character is promoted or otherwise given some significance, but that person or character is still secondary to non-minority persons or characters in that media.
The position that an individual and/or group occupies or is perceived as occupying within a group and/or society.
The ability for LGBTQ persons to be perceived as equal members of society, including media presence of said persons.
The ability for transgender persons to be perceived as equal members of society, including media presence of said persons.
A person who is harmed by another or who suffers from a calamity.

A cultural practice where nonbinary people are erased from cultural narratives. Nonbinary persons may also be ignored within the LGBTQIA+ community (and even within the transgender community) and their identity may not be acknowledged.

A term covering a wide range of transphobic beliefs held by some members of the transgender community. These beliefs essentially distinguish between "true" transgender people (those who experience gender dysphoria, take or will take hormones as part of hormone replacement therapy, and have or will undergo gender confirmation surgery). One of transmedicalism's central beliefs is that gender dysphoria is a medical condition which requires HRT and GCS as treatment and that anyone who says they are trans and does not have dysphoria or does not want HRT or GCS is a "transtrender" or part of a fad.
Social rejection by one's peers.

Social rejection which occurs when a person refuses the romantic advances of another, ignores/avoids or is repulsed by someone who is romantically interested in them, or unilaterally ends an existing relationship.
Social rejection by one's family.
The insertion of a hand into the vagina as part of sexual behavior.
The insertion of a hand into the anus as part of sexual behavior.
The insertion of a hand (or fist) into an orifice (for example, the vagina or anus) as part of sexual behavior.
Sexual intercourse in which the tongue is inserted into the vagina.

A subset of sexual practices in which either real or imagined racial background of a participant or participants is used to justify power imbalance, including, but not limited to, the usage of slurs, racial narratives, and objects imbued with racial meaning.
Pleasure derived from cruelty to non-human animals. It is part of the Macdonald triad, a set of three behaviors that are considered a precursor to psychopathic behavior.

A theoretical concept that describes the use of aspects of marginalized gender expressions in the gender performance or identity of privileged men. Scholarship on hybrid masculinities suggests that they simultaneously distance themselves from traditional norms of masculinity while reproducing and reinforcing hegemonic masculinity.

A socio-political system where (primarily) cisgender males and heterosexuals have authority over cisgender females and over other sexual orientations and gender identities. It is a term that emphasizes that discrimination exerted both upon women and LGBTQ people has the same sexist social principle.

An approach to thinking about masculinity in the context of social changes that have undermined traditional hegemonic masculinity and its associated homophobia, which each have driven men to avoid certain behaviors in order to avoid being publicly perceived as gay; it holds that there are increasingly societal spaces in which men no longer need to behave in hypermasculine ways in order to be accepted.

A complimentary field of thought to ecofeminism. While ecofeminism has traditionally focused on studying issues such as how the exploitation of women and women's bodies is congruent with the exploitation of nature, ecomasculinity studies men's role in this process and looks for ways to enable men to take on roles that would challenge exploitative thought patterns and practices.
Male gender roles classified by culture.
Female gender roles classified by culture.
Masculinities associated with the reign of Queen Victoria over the United Kingdom from 1836 to 1901.
Femininities associated with the reign of Queen Victoria over the United Kingdom from 1836 to 1901.
Sexual arousal that depends on acting out or imagining one's self as an animal. Mostly practiced by wearing an animal costume, such as a latex mask, mascot costume or fursuit.
A person who is albino or who has a condition known as albinism.
Discrimination based on the appearance of somebody's face.
Discrimination against bearded persons.
An act which takes into the account of actions and reactions of individuals (or "agents").
A social behavior that involves the coordinated behavior of large groups as well as emergent properties of these groups.
A social behavior that involves the coordinated behavior of large groups of similar mammals as well as emergent properties of these groups.
A social behavior that involves the coordinated behavior of large groups of similar primates as well as emergent properties of these groups.

Rape or other forms of sexual violence committed by combatants during armed conflict, war, or military occupation often as spoils of war; but sometimes, particularly in ethnic conflict, the phenomenon has broader sociological motives.
The action of a group who has carried out acts of mass rape during wartime against their perceived enemy as part of a genocidal campaign.
A mistaken belief or a wrong idea pertaining to human behavior or behaviors.
A mistaken belief or a wrong idea pertaining to rape.
A situation in which the perpetrator obtains the victim's agreement to engage in sexual intercourse or other sex acts, but gains it by deception or false statements or actions.
A surgery to remove one or both testicles which leaves the glandular tissue that surrounds each testicle in place.
Erotic attraction of a woman or older female toward young girls; lesbian pederasty.
Pederastic relationships and behaviors in ancient Rome, defined by domination and exploitation. With passive roles being undertaken by male prostitutes or slaves who were usually non-Roman.

A genderless language is a natural or constructed language that has no distinctions of grammatical genderthat is, no categories requiring morphological agreement between nouns and associated pronouns, adjectives, articles, or verbs.

Inclusive language used to describe something in a way which isn't inherently gendered (i.e. using "partner" instead of "boyfriend" or "girlfriend" or having all gender or gender-neutral bathrooms instead of bathrooms for only men and women).
Figurative (or non-literal) language uses words in a way that deviates from their conventionally accepted definitions in order to convey a more complicated meaning or heightened effect.
Literal language uses words exactly according to their conventionally accepted meanings or denotation.
A word or phrase that departs from straightforward, literal language.
A figure of speech that relies on the structure of the sentence, unlike the trope, which plays with the meanings of words.
A common plot convention, idea, element or theme as a use of figurative language, via word, phrase or an image, for artistic effect such as using a figure of speech.
The use of a word or phrase to replace another with one that is considered less offensive, blunt or vulgar than the word or phrase which it replaces.
The use of a derogatory, offensive or vulgar word or phrase to replace a (more) neutral original.
